[The WHO meeting, to be held on 16 and 17 Feb 2012 at the WHO's headquarters, will focus on the most basic problems that have arisen as a result of the Avian A/(H5N1) influenza virus controversy. In essence: should the 2 papers at the heart of the dispute be published? In full or in abbreviated form? If they must be abbreviated, which sections must be held back?

Further comment on this topic will be withheld until the outcome of the meeting and the identities of the participants become available. - Mod.CP]]
